'''美国感恩节'''是一个[[美国|美国]]人民每年在11月的第四个周四庆祝的[[感恩节|感恩节]]的一种的公共节日。它起源于[[丰收节|丰收节]]。主要的庆祝活动是[[感恩节大餐|感恩节大餐]]。传统的感恩节大餐包括美洲本土的食物和菜肴，即[[火鸡|火鸡]]、[[马铃薯|土豆]]（通常是[[土豆泥|土豆泥]]）、[[馅|馅料]]、[[南瓜|南瓜]]、[[玉米|玉米]]、[[豆角|豆角]]、[[蔓越莓|蔓越莓]]（通常是[[酱汁|酱汁]]）和[[南瓜派|南瓜派]]。其他感恩节习俗包括慈善组织为穷人提供感恩节大餐，参加宗教仪式，游行，以及观看足球比赛<ref name="Counihan2013">{{cite book |last1=Counihan |first1=Carole |title=Food in the USA: A Reader |date=18 October 2013 |publisher=Routledge |isbn=978-1-135-32359-2 |page=5 |language=en |quote=Football games are scheduled and televised throughout the nation; an elaborately constructed, now traditional Macy's parade may be viewed. There are special services, which some attend, and turkeys and other foods are given by churches and other charitable organizations to the poor.}}</ref>。在美国文化中，感恩节被认为是秋冬假期的开始，其中包括[[圣诞节|圣诞节]]和[[新年|新年]]。

自1789年[[乔治·华盛顿|乔治·华盛顿]]宣布之后，感恩节一直在全国范围内的庆祝。<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/11/28/thanksgiving-proclamation_n_4078958.html|title=Christie's Is Selling The Proclamation That Established Thanksgiving, Signed By George Washington|last=Frank|first=Priscilla|date=November 28, 2013|publisher=Huffington Post|accessdate=6 December 2013|archive-date=2016-11-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161126174826/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/11/28/thanksgiving-proclamation_n_4078958.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>在美国[[南北战争|南北战争]]时期，1863年[[亚伯拉罕·林肯|亚伯拉罕·林肯]]总统发表了“感恩和赞美我们在天堂的天父”的宣告 ，在那之后每年11月的第四个周四便成为了传统的国家庆祝节日。<ref name="NetINS Showcase-AB">{{Cite web|url=http://showcase.netins.net/web/creative/lincoln/speeches/thanks.htm|title=Proclamation of Thanksgiving (October 3, 1863)|accessdate=2010-11-24|publisher=Abraham Lincoln Online|archive-date=2010-01-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100123030743/http://showcase.netins.net/web/creative/lincoln/speeches/thanks.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>与[[圣诞节|圣诞节]]和[[新年|新年]]一同作为广泛的节庆假日的一部分。

美国人通常称之为“第一感恩节”的活动是在1621年他们在[[新大陸|新大陆]]有了第一次收获之后由朝圣者庆祝的。<ref name="bradford85">Bradford, ''Of Plymouth Plantation,1789-1897'', pp. 85–92.</ref> 这次宴会持续了三天，据参会者爱德华温斯洛<ref>{{Citation|last=Winslow|first=Edward|title=Mourt's Relation|url=http://factreal.files.wordpress.com/2009/11/heritagepilgrimsmourtsrelationjournalbywinslow.pdf|year=1622|quote=many of the Indians coming amongst us, and amongst the rest their greatest king Massasoyt, with some ninetie men, whom for three dayes we entertained and feasted|page=133|access-date=2013-11-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151125220402/https://factreal.files.wordpress.com/2009/11/heritagepilgrimsmourtsrelationjournalbywinslow.pdf|archive-date=2015-11-25|dead-url=yes}}</ref>所说，宴会有90个美洲原住民和53个朝圣者参加。<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.pilgrimhallmuseum.org/pdf/TG_What_Happened_in_1621.pdf|title=Primary Sources for "The First Thanksgiving" at Plymouth|accessdate=2009-11-26|publisher=Pilgrim Hall Museum|quote=The 53 Pilgrims at the First Thanksgiving|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121224003144/http://www.pilgrimhallmuseum.org/pdf/TG_What_Happened_in_1621.pdf|archive-date=2012-12-24|dead-url=yes}}</ref><span class="cx-segment" data-segmentid="72">[[新英格兰|新英格兰]]殖民者习惯于定期庆祝“[[感恩节|感恩节]]” - 祷告感谢上帝的祝福，如军事胜利或干旱的结束。</span> 
