== 历史 ==

=== 早期感恩节活动 ===
抽时间感谢别人的祝福，或是举行节日庆祝收获，都是早在欧洲人定居北美之前的做法。根据历史学家詹姆斯·贝克所说，任何发生在现代美国领土的“第一感恩节”都像一粒豆瓣中的暴风雨。<ref name="Baker">{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=yoMhqK9Z5HwC&dq|title=Thanksgiving: the biography of an American holiday|last=Baker|first=James W.|publisher=UPNE|year=2009|isbn=9781584658016|page=273|access-date=2016-11-18|archive-date=2019-01-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190107083748/https://books.google.com/books?id=yoMhqK9Z5HwC&dq%20|dead-url=no}}</ref>

在目前属于美国的领土上的第一个有记载的感恩服务是由西班牙人<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.churchmilitant.com/news/article/catholics-did-it-first |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2016-11-18 |archive-date=2016-09-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160922171342/http://www.churchmilitant.com/news/article/catholics-did-it-first |dead-url=no }}</ref>和法国人<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2008/11/26/opinion/26davis.html?th&emc=th|title=A French Connection|last=Davis|first=Kenneth C.|date=November 25, 2008|publisher=Nytimes.com|accessdate=2011-09-05|archive-date=2012-06-29|archive-url=https://archive.today/20120629021805/http://www.nytimes.com/2008/11/26/opinion/26davis.html?_r=1&th&emc=th|dead-url=no}}</ref>在16世纪做出的。

